  "prompt": "IRMA ANAND cutoff?",
  "response": "The cutoff for admission to IRMA (Institute of Rural Management Anand) varies each year based on various factors such as the number of applicants, difficulty level of the entrance exam, and the specific program. Typically, IRMA accepts scores from the CAT, XAT, and its own entrance exam, the IRMA Entrance Exam (IRMASAT).\n\nFor the most accurate and up-to-date information on cutoffs for a specific year or program, I recommend checking IRMA's official website or contacting their admissions office directly. They usually publish detailed cutoff information for their various programs after the entrance exam results are announced.",
